unittitle.value: Records of the Bureau of Public Occasions

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: The Records of the Bureau of Public Occasions contain a wide array of information related to the planning and hosting of University public events, commencement and commencement-related programs. The records are arranged alphabetically in one series and consist mainly of administrative records, correspondence, drafts, notes, telegraphs and photo contact sheets.

p.value: Permission to publish materials must be obtained in writing from the: New York University Archives, Elmer Holmes Bobst Library, 70 Washington Square South, New York, NY 10012, Phone: (212) 998-2646, Fax: (212) 995-4070, E-mail: university.archives@library.nyu.edu

Identification of item, date (if known); Records of the Office of the Bureau of Public Occasions; RG 4.2; box number; folder number; New York University Archives Elmer Holmes Bobst Library 70 Washington Square South, New York, NY 10012, New York University Libraries.

Frusciano, Thomas J. and Marilyn H. Pettit,

Some documents, mostly correspondence, in the folders relating to NYU in Puerto Rico are in Spanish.
